article.description: Javion Ogunyemi scored 23 points and Siena pulled away from Niagara 75-63 on Saturday.
article.headline: Siena pulls away from Niagara 75-63
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Javion Ogunyemi scored 23 points and Siena pulled away from Niagara 75-63 on Saturday. Ogunyemi was 7 of 11 from the floor, 9 of 10 from the line and grabbed 11 rebounds. Brett Bisping added 20 points for the Saints (9-5, 2-1 Metro Atlantic), and Lavon Long had 12 points, nine boards and six assists. Siena won the rebound battle 37-21. Emile Blackman led Niagara with 19 points. Marvin Prochet had 16 points and Matt Scott added 14. Niagara closed the first half with a 7-2 spurt and led at halftime 34-30. Siena quickly erased the deficit in the second half, and Oqunyemi's jumper with 4:34 left put the Saints up by nine. Cameron Fowler's 3-pointer with 2:43 left pulled Niagara within six, but the Purple Eagles got no closer.
